					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Parchment codex of the 14th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="perg">
								<extent>547 folios <dimensions unit="mm" type="leaf">
										<height>340</height>
										<width>251</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>222</height>
										<width>160</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>547 folios (+ 2 modern paper flyleaves at the beginning and 3 at the end). </p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>55 quires of originally 10 leaves each, numbered with Hebrew letters at the end. </p>
									<p>1 leaf of the 1st quire, 3 leaves of the 7th, and 1 leaf of the last quire have been cancelled. </p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>Stained. </p>
									<p>Incomplete. </p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="2" ruledLines="42" writtenLines="42">
									<p>Uniform layout. Last written line outside ruling. </p>
									<p>Pricking and page by page ruling (horizontal in ink and vertical in plummet) is visible.  </p>
									<p>Hair-side and flesh-side of folios distinguishable. Scratching and hair follicles visible. </p>
									<p>Chapter initials and titles given in larger characters.  </p>
									<p>Headings and catchwords (in smaller characters) in each page. </p>
									<p>Occasional marginal notes and additions. </p>
									<p>Folio 1r-v has a summary of Mishneh Torah. </p>
									<p>Several diagrams have not been completed (e.g. 289r). </p>
									<p>Many erasures.</p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="1">
							<summary>Sefardi square and semi-cursive script (at variance with production area) of the 15th century. <name type="person" role="scribe">Yesha῾yah ben Ya῾aḳov mi-Masr᾿an</name>: inscribed in the colophon: folio 547r. </summary>
							<handNote script="Hebrew" scope="sole"/>
						</handDesc>
						<additions>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="patron">Mosheh ha-Leṿi ben Sha᾿ul ha-Leṿi</name>: inscribed, folio 547r. A contract of sale of the manuscript to the descendants of the patron's family, folio 547v.</p>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="owner">Mordekhai ben Yosef Kohen</name>: inscribed, folio 12r.</p>
							<p>Censored by <name type="person" role="censor">Domenico Irosolimitano</name>, Italian censor (active in the last quarter of the 16th and first quarter of the 17th century): inscribed with his name, (folio 547r); see <ref target="Popper_1969" type="page">61</ref>, and appendix § 62-74.
</p>
							<p>Censored by <name type="person" role="censor">Giovanni Domenico Carretto</name>, Italian censor (active in the first quarter of the 17th century): inscribed with his name (folio 547v); see <ref target="Popper_1969" type="page">100-101</ref>, and appendix § 80-84. </p>
						</additions>
						<bindingDesc>
							<binding>
								<p>BM in-house. Red cover.</p>
								<p>Spine title: 'Maimonides. Yadh Hahazakah. Hebrew. Brit. Mus. Harley 5719.'</p>
							</binding>
						</bindingDesc>
